# TypeScript Standards for AI Lab

## File Structure Template
Every TypeScript file must follow this structure:

```typescript
/**
 * @fileoverview Brief description of file purpose and main functionality
 * @author Your Name
 * @created YYYY-MM-DD
 */

// External imports (libraries, frameworks)
import React from 'react'
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server'

// Internal imports (grouped by type)
import { ChatMessage } from '@/types/chat'
import { useChatStore } from '@/stores/chat-store'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

// Type definitions and interfaces
interface ComponentProps {
  // ... prop definitions
}

// Main implementation
```

## Function Documentation
All functions require comprehensive JSDoc comments:

```typescript
/**
 * Brief function description
 * @description Detailed explanation of functionality and behavior
 * @param paramName - Parameter description with type info
 * @returns Promise/value description with type info
 * @throws {ErrorType} When specific error conditions occur
 * @example
 * ```typescript
 * const result = await functionName(param)
 * console.log(result)
 * ```
 */
```

## Type Definitions
- Use interfaces for object shapes
- Use types for unions and computed types
- Use enums for constants with semantic meaning
- Use const assertions for immutable data
- Prefer generic types for reusable components

## Import Organization
1. External libraries (React, Next.js, third-party)
2. Internal types (from @/types)
3. Internal utilities (from @/lib)
4. Internal components (from @/components)
5. Internal hooks (from @/hooks)
6. Internal stores (from @/stores)
7. Relative imports (same directory)